tweet: Congress must pursue the facts wherever they lead. Based on that evidence, the House’s inquiry may lead to the president’s eventual impeachment. That is right and proper, because no one is above the law, including the President of the United States.

I have sworn an oath to protect and defend the Constitution against all enemies, foreign and domestic. That is why I continue to support the House's methodical, thorough, and factual impeachment inquiry.
President Trump's actions have raised profound concerns that he has abused his power, betrayed our national security, and corrupted our electoral process – all for his personal political gain.
Today is a sad day for America. It gave me no joy to vote today to move to the next phase of the impeachment inquiry against President Trump, but he has left me no choice.
